column1: #Text=The dive site Manta Reef is an offshore rocky reef with coral in the Guinjata Bay area , near Inhambane in Southern Mozambique .
#Text=This is a site with lots of fish and invertebrates , and has three manta cleaning stations .
#Text=It has become famous for close encounters with manta rays .
#Text=About 4km north of Ponta Gumula and 10.5km north of the launch site at Guinjata Bay
#Text=The name " Manta Reef " is a reference to the Manta rays thet are often seen there .
#Text=The top of the reef is about 18m .
#Text=topography , comprising a tabular rock reef bordered by sand bottom .
#Text=Most of the reef is bout 3 or 4m high with relatively flat top .
#Text=Edges quite scalloped and ragged with outcrops and boulders with crevices and overhangs .
#Text=To the north is Manta Pinnacles , which is a massive rock that rises from about 26 m on the sand to 18 m on top .
#Text=There is a wall of 8 m with a swim-through and a large overhang .
#Text=To the south there is a wall that drops down to 30m on the sand , with lots of cracks and ledges .
#Text=Currents and surge rarely affect this reef , but occasionally a current may make it difficult to follow a planned dive profile , and the dive plan may be altered to suit conditions .
#Text=The site is only accessible by boat
#Text=The site is 4.2 km from Coconut Bay Beach Launch Site , about 10.2km from Guinjata Bay beach launch site , and about 24km from Barra Lodge .
#Text=Large variety of reef fish and various invertebrates .
#Text=There are three cleaning stations that are regularly used by Mantas .
#Text=A large Potato bass is resident in this area .
#Text=Manta Canyon is another station where mantas are cleaned by Cleaner wrasse , Goldies and Butterflyfish .

#Text=Fish seen at this site include : Potato bass , Bluebanded snapper , Guitarfish , Parrot fish , Scorpion fish , Coachman , Big scale soldier , Trumpet fish , Two bar clownfish , Longnose butterfly fish , Raccoon butterfly fish , Threadfin butterflyfish , White spotted butterflyfish , Gorgeous gussy , Pearly butterfly fish , Goldies , Brownspotted rock cod , Moorish idol , Chocolate chip , Devil ray .

#Text=Boxy , Longhead flathead ( Crocodile fish ) , Leopard and Giant morays , Scorpionfish , Flame goatfish , Powder blue surgeon , Blue tangs , Triggerfish , schools of Yellow snappers , Bigeyes , Longnose hawkfish , and Fusiliers .
#Text=Thistle soft coral , Daisy soft coral , Pink arch sponge , plate corals , Turret coral , Mushroom coral .

#Text=Blocked starfish , Crown of thorns star , Olive green warty star , Black long spined urchin , banded feather stars , Black sea cucumber , Sandy sea cucumber , a large pinkish cucumber with dark blotchy back , Giant anemone , various sponges , sea squirts , White feather duster worms , Peacock shrimp , Spanish dancer nudibranchs , and eggshell cowries ,
#Text=The boat ride also offers the opportunity to spot whale sharks and dolphins .
#Text=Macro , wide angle , and anything in between .
#Text=Artificial lighting will bring back the true colour .
#Text=Dives at this site are almost exclusively organised by operators who supply a divemaster to guide the dive , and who will show you the route .
#Text=DSMB and reel can be useful if you have to surface away from the group .
